=========================================
Installing ONIE on Freescale T2080RDB
=========================================

Cross-Compiling ONIE
====================
  $ cd build-config
  $ make -j4 MACHINE=fsl_p2020rdbpca all

When complete, the ONIE binaries are located in 'build/images':
  -rw-r--r--   786432 Aug 26 11:25  fsl_t2080rdb-r0.u-boot
  -rw-r--r-- 11272192 Aug 26 11:25  onie-fsl_t2080rdb-r0.bin


Installing the ONIE binaries
============================
A single binary image needs to be installed on the NOR flash.

Image -- ONIE kernel, u-boot, dtb and ramdisk
name:  onie-fsl_t2080rdb-r0.bin


First put the ONIE files on a TFTP server, the following directions
assume the files are on the root of the TFTP server.
ONIE defaults the serial console baud rate to 115200.
You may need to adjust your terminal settings.


Step 1 -- Update uboot image
---------------------------------
 => tftpboot fsl_t2080rdb-r0.u-boot
 => protect off eff40000 +$filesize
 => erase eff40000 +$filesize
 => cp.b 1000000 eff40000 $filesize
 => reset


Step 2 -- Install onie-fsl_t2080rdb-r0.bin
------------------------------------------
Copying the image using TFTP and flash to the NOR flash::
  => tftp onie-fsl_t2080rdb-r0.bin
  => protect off $onie_start +${onie_sz.b} && erase $onie_start +${onie_sz.b}
  => cp.b $loadaddr $onie_start ${onie_sz.b} && protect on $onie_start +${onie_sz.b}


Step 3 -- Restart The System
----------------------------
You can interrupt the boot process by pressing any key during the count down:
  => reset


Step 4 -- Optional
------------------
By default the system will start the ONIE in *install* mode.  After
booting press the [Enter] key to active the console.

Alternatively you can start the system in *rescue* mode so you can
login and look around the ONIE.  To start the rescue mode type this:
  => setenv reboot_cmd rescue
  => boot
